00:06:01.890 --> 00:06:06.740
Immanuel Mifsud was
born in Malta in 1967.

00:06:06.740 --> 00:06:11.040
He has published eight poetry
collections, including a collection

00:06:11.040 --> 00:06:18.310
of travel poems, Km, kilometer, in
bilingual edition with translations

00:06:18.310 --> 00:06:22.690
by Maria Grech Ganado,
and Confidential Reports,

00:06:22.690 --> 00:06:25.780
which was published in
Ireland with translations

00:06:25.780 --> 00:06:30.950 position:56%
by Maurice Riordan and Adrian Grima.

00:06:30.950 --> 00:06:33.020
I'm sorry for my pronunciation.

00:06:33.020 --> 00:06:37.960
He has also published 10
collections of short stories,

00:06:37.960 --> 00:06:42.320
including Sara Sue
Sammut's Strange Stories,

00:06:42.320 --> 00:06:47.400
which won the National
Literary Award for 2002,

00:06:47.400 --> 00:06:51.050
and was later short-listed
for the Premio Strega Europa.

00:06:51.050 --> 00:06:55.760
Of course he is very
well-known internationally

00:06:55.760 --> 00:07:01.400
for his award-winning novel, In
The Name of the Father and the Son,

00:07:01.400 --> 00:07:06.510
which won the European
Prize in 2011.

